From fb01a835e7a87b6eb7bb21e70c472357f9be004a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 7 Jul 2025 23:15:09 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/9] Upstream: DP: wifi: ath12k: add page fragment support in
 monitor path

Currently, the driver allocates an skb for each frame received in the
monitor destination ring, leading to higher memory consumption, especially
in extended statistics and monitor modes. In extended statistics mode,
hardware copies TLV tags and data into the skb->data area, leaving other
members of the struct sk_buff unused and unnecessarily consuming memory.
Similarly, in monitor mode, when AMSDU frames are received, all MSDUs
are allocated within the struct sk_buff, which is inefficient.

To address this, introduce fragmented memory allocation. Using the
page fragment approach, payloads and TLVs are stored in 2K-sized page
fragments, optimizing memory usage.

Patch-dependency:
0475-03-Upstream-DP-wifi-ath12k-Utilize-monitor-descriptor-d.patch

Signed-off-by: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
